underlying_goal: Design an experiment and implementation plan to improve the Trusted Monitor baseline for an ICML paper by aggregating its scores across paraphrases.
primary_success: Identified that the core required infrastructure was 90% present and designed a minimal, targeted implementation plan focusing only on the missing pre-aggregation step, while also refining the experimental protocol for rigor.
brief_summary: The user proposed improving the Trusted Monitor (TM) baseline by aggregating scores across paraphrases. The agent explored the codebase, found that most infrastructure already existed, and designed a focused plan to add the missing pre-aggregation step. The plan was iteratively refined to ensure a rigorous experimental design for an ICML paper submission.
